            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Network Rail Telecommunications operates the UK Rail Telecommunications systems owned by Network Rail. Multi-billion pound investments have seen the deployment of what is now the second largest private telecommunications network in the UK. The systems provide fixed and radio (track to train) telecommunications systems used for the safe and efficient use of the operational rail network.</P>
               <P>A further 1 000 000 000 GBP is earmarked for telecommunications investment in Control Period 6, from 2019 to 2024, with an emphasis on improving the IP capabilities of what is a predominantly SDH network today.</P>
               <P>The continued investment in the rail telecommunications infrastructure will require Network Rail Telecommunications to seek skilled engineering support from industry to strengthen its own design capability. Network Rail intends to create a Framework contract under which to let Commission Contracts as required.</P>
